Durban - Mohammed Vahed Ebrahim,  the man accused of kidnapping Miguel Louw is back in the Durban Magistrates Court this morning.
 

 Miguel, 11, was allegedly kidnapped earlier this year. His body was found buried in a shallow grave in September.

 

 The 43-year-old told media he was in a relationship with Miguel's mother Raylene and was very close to the child.

 

 The Phoenix resident, who earlier this month maintained 
 he learnt of Miguel's death while in prison, said he received threatening messages and calls while on bail.





 
 AdChoicesADVERTISINGinRead invented by Teads


 

 The case has been postponed to December.

 
  







